&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="grow"&gt;
 笔记
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="admonition-content mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-inherit"&gt;&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;bootloader&lt;/strong&gt; is a program responsible for loading the operating system kernel into memory and starting the operating system. It operates at the low level, interfacing directly with the system&amp;rsquo;s firmware (e.g., BIOS/UEFI).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>